thread.title: Cedar Woods increases WA holding

author: Simon Johanson
title: Cedar Woods increases WA holding
text:
Perth-based greenfield developer Cedar Woods has increased its landholding in Western Australia, buying 50.74 hectares in Baldivis on the outskirts of Rockingham.
Cedar Woods paid $26.25 million plus GST and will settle on the site at the end of August, the group said in a statement.
The land covers three titles and is next to another 68-hectare parcel owned by Cedar Woods to the south. Combined they will cover 119 hectares west of the Kwinana Freeway.
The group expects the site will yield about 700 residential lots ranging between 225 and 550 square metres.
The property developer has recently been embroiled in controversy after gaining partial approval for a mega development in Queensland's Upper Kedron last week.
The Queensland government approved an initial 480 lots but the decision by the previous administration to approve a much larger development had sparked a community backlash.
